        "requirement": "You have a creature grabbed or restrained.",
        "critical_success": "You throw the creature any distance up to 10 feet, plus 5 feet \u00d7 your Strength modifier. It takes bludgeoning damage equal to your Strength modifier plus 1d6 per 10 feet you threw it. If you threw the target at least 10 feet and into a solid obstacle, use the maximum distance you could have thrown it to calculate the damage. The creature falls prone.",
        "success": "As critical success, but the creature doesn't fall prone.",
        "failure": "You don't throw the creature.",
        "critical_failure": "You don't throw the creature, and it's no longer grabbed or restrained by you.",
        "archetype_level": 8,
